npm commands:

1. npm ls
  You can check all the node modules and their dependencies
  
2. npm config get prefix
  You can get the gloabl folder of your node modules, like C:\Users\jhao\AppData\Roaming\npm
  
3. npm outdated
  Check the versions of all the node modules 
  
4. npm install [@<scope>/]<name>@<version>
  npm install a specific version of the module, check this link: https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install
  
5. npm install lodash --save
  Use --save flag to update the package.json file after npm install
  
  npm uninstall lodash --save
  The same, if you want to uninstall and remove the dependecy from package.json file, you still need --save flag 
  
6.
